    "name": "Rhinoceros",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The rhinoceros feeds on leafy plants, branches, and even thorny shrubs. Its thick hide is a mottled gray color, and it can run surprisingly fast for a beast of its size. The rhinoceros is notoriously short-tempered and prone to attacking anything it perceives as approaching too closely (generally within a distance of 80 feet\u2014the distance of a single charge\u2014for most rhinos)."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This rhinoceros has a low-slung head with twisted ears that lie back along its neck.</i>",
